speech.p:
1. The payment out of money provided by Parliament of—




(1) any increase attributable to the raising by the Act to £3,000,000 of the limit on the aggregate amount of grants that may be made to the Co-operative Development Agency ('the Agency') by the Secretary of State under section 4 of the Co-operative Development Agency Act 1978;

(2) any sums required for defraying the liabilities of the Agency after its dissolution;

(3) any sums required by the Secretary of State for making grants in respect of projects of investment in undertakings being projects—


(a) which are approved by the Secretary of State;

(b) whose purposes are to create new or expand existing productive capacity or to effect a change in the product or in the process of producing it; and

(c) which are to provide assets or jobs in development areas.
